      <title>The kingdom vs Sony alpha 900</title>
      <link>http://www.pitslamp.com/blog/20110503_the_kingdom</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 03 May 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://www.pitslamp.com/blog/20110503_the_kingdom</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A couple of weeks ago, Sony gave me a alpha 900 to test during some weeks. As is becoming a habit lately I&amp;rsquo;m not very into reviewing the technical aspects or comparing it to other cameras. Instead I try the camera in a real life situation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve been looking into a making a stop-motion video for some time now. So this was the perfect opportunity to try this out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I didn&amp;rsquo;t want to make just any stop-motion, but do it as a kind of a video clip for a song with a meaning. So I chose The kingdom of &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.milow.com&#34; title=&#34;milow&#34; rel=&#34;contact met&#34;&gt;Milow&lt;/a&gt;. A number about the current political situation in Belgium&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have a look at the result below. Just to be clear it is not the official video of The Kingdom.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://vimeo.com/23018445&#34;&gt;Proof of concept: Milow &amp;#8211; The Kingdom&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&#34;http://vimeo.com/pitslamp&#34;&gt;PitsLamp&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=&#34;http://vimeo.com&#34;&gt;Vimeo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It took me 13 hours to make the video and couldn&amp;rsquo;t have done it without the help of my great girlfriend. Also I asked and got permission of Milow to use his song in this video, which I&amp;rsquo;m very grateful for.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
